# auto-api-rust — Cursor Rules

- Rust edition 2021, deps: reqwest (json), serde, serde_json
- tokio is dev-dependency only (for examples)
- Client struct, 6 async methods returning Result<T, Error>
- Error enum: Auth, Api, Network variants
- impl From<reqwest::Error> for automatic ? conversion
- Option<String> for optional params, ..Default::default() pattern
- serde_json::Value for raw offer data — varies between sources
- snake_case, pub fields on response structs
- Rustdoc (///) on every public item, in English
- All code comments and docs in English

## Key Files

- src/lib.rs — re-exports
- src/client.rs — Client struct (6 async methods)
- src/types.rs — all types + OffersParams
- src/error.rs — Error enum
- Cargo.toml — manifest

## Never

- Use unwrap() in library code
- Add tokio as main dependency
- Use panic! in library code
- Skip Rustdoc on public items
